sequenceDiagram
    participant RP as RadarController (process)
    participant Q as pt_fft_q
    participant BC as BedMonitorController
    participant RE as RadarEngine
    participant GUI as MainWindow / Respiration GUI
    participant POL as App Policy (robot/alerts)

    RP->>Q: (1) Push new radar frame<br/>Out: raw complex frame
    BC->>Q: (2) Pull available frames<br/>In: queue frames, Out: frame batch
    BC->>RE: (3) Run batch through engine<br/>In: frames + config + pose
    RE-->>BC: (4) Return typed EngineOutput<br/>Out: activity/respiration/vitals models
    BC-->>GUI: (5) Publish GUI payload<br/>Out: app-facing dicts for plots/badges
    BC-->>POL: (6) Publish policy events<br/>Out: zone/posture/motion_score/fall state
    POL-->>BC: (7) Optional pose request<br/>In: policy trigger, Out: pose update command
    BC->>RE: (8) Apply radar pose<br/>In: pose transform, Out: used by next frame cycle

    Note over BC,RE: Runtime pose formula (concept): world_xyz = T_pose x sensor_xyz.
    Note over BC,GUI: Boundary rule: GUI receives translated dicts; typed engine models stay inside controller.
